annotationA: 6-phosphogluconate dehydrogenase, decarboxylating; Phosphogluconate dehydrogenase (Pgd) is a cytosolic enzyme that catalyzes the oxidation of 6-phosphogluconate to ribulose 5-phosphate, with the concomitant reduction of NADP(+) to NADPH. Pgd and Zw are the two NADP(+) reducing enzymes in the pentose phosphate pathway
annotationB: Phosphoglucomutase; This enzyme participates in both the breakdown and synthesis of glucose; Belongs to the phosphohexose mutase family
